# Template for frontend/.env.prod — the production build config.
#
#   cp .env.prod.example .env.prod      # then edit the values below
#
# .env.prod is git-ignored (repo convention) but IS read by the production Docker
# build (`vite build --mode prod`). VITE_* values are inlined into the public client
# bundle at build time, so they are NOT secrets — real secrets stay on the backend.
#
# The Docker build FAILS if this file is absent and no VITE_API_URL build-arg is
# passed, so a prod image never silently ships the localhost dev fallback.
#
# Same-origin default: the SPA calls the API at /v1 on its own origin, which nginx
# (or your ingress) proxies to the backend. Point it elsewhere for a cross-origin
# API, e.g.  VITE_API_URL=https://api.acme.com/v1
VITE_API_URL=/v1
